==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chromous
<hw>Chro"mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of, pertaining to,
or derived from, chromium, when this element has a valence lower than
that in chromic compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Chromous acid</b></col>, <cd>a bluish gray powder,
CrO.OH, of weak acid properties and regard as an acid.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chromule</ent>⟦br⟧
